{
  "texts": [
    "The best performing LLM is Mixtral-8x7B with NTP (16.1% Very good, 33.7% Good), the worst ones being GPT-4-Turbo (1% Very good, 9% Good) and Mixtral-8x7B-Instruct with NTP.",
    "Of all the modelstrategy combinations, only Mixtral-8x7B-NTP and Llama-3-70B (NTP or FA) perform similarly or (marginally) better than the random permutation baseline (14% Very good, 32% Good).",
    "Differences between NTP and FA generation strategies is discussed in Appendix D.1.",
    "Lastly, for the two models on which we ran both the foundational and the instruct versions (Llama-3-8B and Mixtral-8x7B), the instruct models performed significantly worse: less than 2% Very good, less than 12% Good.",
    "We present a multidimensional scaling (MDS) projection in Figures S2, S3"
  ]
}